  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink259-kilavi">varaiyat tuṇinta talaimakaṉ varaivu muṭittaṟkut talaimakaḷ varuntukiṉṟa varuttam tōḻi kāṭṭak kaṇṭu iṉi yatu kaṭuka muṭiyum eṉa vuvanta vuḷḷattaṉāyt taṉṉuḷḷē colliyatu.
          </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">What the hero, who had resolved to marry, said within himself, having seen as the confidante showed [him] the heroine’s distress [at the delay] in completing the marriage, and becoming inwardly glad that now it could be quickly accomplished.   
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink259">
<l>kuṉṟak kuṟavaṉ kātaṉ maṭamakaṇ</l>
<l>maṉṟa vēṅkai malarcila koṇṭu</l>
<l>malaiyuṟai kaṭavuḷ kulamutal vaḻuttit</l>
<l>tēmpalic ceyta vīrnaṟuṅ kaiyaṇ</l>
<l>malarnta kānta ṇāṟik</l>
<l>kaliḻnta kaṇṇaḷem maṇaṅki yōḷē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>The beloved, naïve daughter of the hill-dweller—</l>
        <l>she with wet, fragrant hands, who,</l>
        
        <l rend="space">having taken a few blossoms</l>
        <l>of the kino tree in the village common,</l>
        <l>and having praised the family deity,</l>
        <l>the god who dwells in the mountain,</l>
        <l>made offerings of honey—</l>
        
        <l rend="space">being fragrant like blooming Malabar glory lilies,</l>
        <l>she with eyes that have wept—</l>
        
        <l rend="space">is the one who has tormented us.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
